<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua On Patriotism (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 100 education bases provide people with historical
information on the Chinese nation's patriotic tradition through
generation after generation, and improving continuously, the
commentary said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese nation regards contributing all of one's energy to
the construction and protection of the motherland as the greatest
glory, and harming national interest and dignity as the greatest
wrong.
</P>
<P>
This is a lofty national sentiment and a major source of
strength that helps the nation survive and develop. With this
patriotic feeling, our country has beat off invaders and has built
an independent socialist country.
</P>
<P>
During the period of the reforms and opening-up, we should
continue to hold high the banner of patriotism and put all
national strength into building the country.
</P>
<P>
Holding high the banner of patriotism will help us adhere to
the basic national policy of opening up, absorb the best of other
civilizations and cultures, and introduce the advanced foreign
science and technology to accelerate the national development and
progress.
</P>
<P>
It will help us stand firm in the face of difficulties and
setbacks, maintain national dignity and confidence, and turn love
for the motherland into selfless contribution and the
determination to build a strong country.
</P>
<P>
It will also help maintain national unity and the unity of
various ethnic groups, and safeguard people's interests with
patriotism. Making young people aware of patriotism will help them
learn the glorious history of the motherland and help them turn
their patriotic feelings into ideals to contribute to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
"I am a son of the Chinese people, I love my motherland and
people deeply," the commentary quoted the late leader Deng
Xiaoping. The Chinese people should follow his example and make
their own contribution to the building of socialism with Chinese
characteristics, the commentary said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
