<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sakurauchi Hails Hong Kong's Return to Motherland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Yoshio Sakurauchi, Chairman of
Japan's Association for the Promotion of International Trade,
today hailed the coming return of Hong Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
In a speech, Sakurauchi congratulated China on the coming
historical day, July 1, when Hong Kong returns to the embrace of
the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Sakurauchi mentioned a photo collection book on the Opium War
between Britain and China in 1840, during which Chinese people had
to take arms against the oppression of Britain which started the
war to protect its exports of opium to China.
</P>
<P>
Sakurauchi said the book made him understand the sufferings
China had experienced during the war.
</P>
<P>
It is understandable, Sakurauchi said, that the Chinese people
welcome the return of Hong Kong to the motherland with such
immeasurable joy since the island fell under the colonial rule of
Britain soon after the war.
</P>
<P>
Sakurauchi said he believed a brand new age was waiting for
Hong Kong after July 1, just as Hong Kong Chief Executive Tung
Chee Hwa said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the concern of some of the 25,000 Japanese living
in Hong Kong about their life after the return, the chairman said
he was confident that Hong Kong will maintain its role as Asia's
finance, trade, transportation and information center, under the
principle of "one country, two systems", proposed by the late
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Sakurauchi said Hong Kong, known as "the Pearl of the East,"
will shine more brightly after its return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Sakurauchi expressed hope that Hong Kong's return would lead
China one big step forward to its ultimate goal of reunifying of
the whole territory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
