<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Parliament Begins Budget Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Jatiya Sangsad (parliament) of
Bangladesh began its budget session this afternoon while Speaker
Humayun Rashid Chowdhury sought cooperation from all political
parties for the smooth functioning of this session.
</P>
<P>
He said in his opening speech that the current session is very
important as the one-year economic development and activities of
the government will be discussed and decisions will be taken in
this regard.
</P>
<P>
Chowdhury said in a parliamentary democracy, parliament is the
focal point of all activities. "We shall achieve success in the
parliament only when all members of the ruling and opposition
parties will go ahead targeting the national progress and
development," he added.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, Finance Minister Shah AMS Kibria will place the
national budget for the fiscal 1997-98 before the House. This will
be the second budget of the Awami (people's) League government
which came to power through the June 12 election of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Sources said the finance minister is unlikely to propose fresh
taxes but most likely to expand the tax-net. The growth rate in
the gross domestic product is expected to be fixed around 6
percent in the national budget, the sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
