<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chirac Wishes Ratification of EU Stability Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- President Jacques Chirac today
expressed his wish that the European Union (EU) monetary stability
pact be ratified at the EU summit in Amsterdam to be held on June
16 and 17.
</P>
<P>
But he also said that the French government is justified to
stress the need to build a European social model and improve
economic coordinations among EU countries.
</P>
<P>
The French Minister of Economy and Finance Dominique
Strauss-Kahn said on Monday at the EU Council of Economy and
Finance in Luxembourg that France wants to delay the ratification
of the stability pact, because its present text fails to includes
policies on employment and economic coordination among EU
countries.
</P>
<P>
The stability pact, which is aimed at punishing those EU
countries with excessive public deficits after the launching of
the European single currency, is approved by all other 14 EU
members.
</P>
<P>
After having a meeting with Dutch Prime Minister Wim Kok in
Paris today, Chirac said that France remains committed to the goal
of launching the euro on January 1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
"That means that we should examine in Amsterdam, on the one
hand the pact of stability and growth which I hope will be
ratified in Amsterdam, and on the other hand the social models and
coordination of economic policies which, justifiably, the French
government has just emphasized," said Chirac.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that France presented a memorandum on a European
social model two years ago.
</P>
<P>
"I relayed to the president of the (European) Union (Prime
Minister Kok) the worries, the concerns and the requests of the
French government on the last point," said Chirac. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
