<DOCNO> XIE19970611.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Provides Humanitarian Aid for Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said on
Tuesday that it had approved humanitarian aid worth ECU
400,000(one ECU equals 1.13 US dollars) for landmine victims in
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia is one of the most densely mined countries in the
world. After years of war, civilian populations are now the main
casualties of anti-personnel mines. About one in 300 Cambodians
has a landmine injury.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission said that the grant would enable a
Belgian non-governmental organization to run six existing centers
fitting landmine victims with artificial limbs, and to set up a
new center in Banteay Meanchey, the most heavily mined province in
the country.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the Commission also approved humanitarian aid
worth ECU 470,000 for Burkina Faso to combat a meningitis epidemic
in the country.
</P>
<P>
Two other projects approved by the Commission were food aid for
Chad(ECU 270,000) and Guinea Bissau(ECU 60,000).  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
