<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Stresses Work of Party Building, Moral Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today called on schools to continue to enhance the work of party
building and promote cultural and ethical progress in order to
help students become more qualified successors to China's
socialist cause.
</P>
<P>
"This is the fundamental task for the schools, as it concerns
the success of the strategy of revitalizing the nation with
science and education, as well as the future of the country," said
Jiang, who is also the General Secretary of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks in a meeting here with representatives
of a national conference on party building in higher education
institutions, and another national conference on moral education
in primary and middle schools.
</P>
<P>
The president said that schools have made remarkable
achievements in instilling in the minds of teachers and students
Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, promoting cultural and ethical progress in the
schools, and advancing education reform and development. He also
praised schools for their great contribution to China's opening-up
and modernization.
</P>
<P>
With the promotion of socialist cultural and ethical progress
as an important goal of and a basic guarantee for building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, Jiang said that schools
should play a leading role in promoting cultural and ethical
progress for all of society.
</P>
<P>
The president urged schools to use Hong Kong's imminent return
as a foundation for carrying out intensive patriotism education
among their students. This will help them understand China's long
history and culture, especially the history of Chinese people's
struggle for national independence and revitalization over the
past 150 years, he said.
</P>
<P>
Studying hard and contributing to the motherland's socialist
modernization will nurture in students the sense of mission and
responsibility, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the meeting were Hu Jintao, Standing
Committee member of the Political Bureau and member of the
Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee; and Li Lanqing, member
of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and
vice-premier.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
