<HEADLINE> Pak Current Account Deficit to Reach 4.6 Bln Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's current account
deficit is expected to reach 4.6 billion US dollars as against the
target of 3.2 billion dollars by the end of 1996-97 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The trade deficit is being calculated to be 3.6 billion dollars
in the current fiscal year ending June 30. The export is projected
to be 8.4 billion dollars as against the import of 12 billion
dollars, according to the latest report by the Central Board of
State Bank of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Net deficit on services account during the first three quarters
of the current fiscal year was 3 billion dollars compared with 2.6
billion dollars during the same period last year and the initial
target of 3.6 billion dollars for the whole fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that deficit of services account by the end of
1996-97 fiscal year may reach 3.8 billion dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
