<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's 100 Model Bases For Patriotic Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Propaganda Department of the
Chinese Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee has announced the
namelist of 100 model bases for patriotic education, said a
leading official of the department.
</P>
<P>
The official told Xinhua that the move was aimed at making
these bases play a larger role in China's patriotic education
drive.
</P>
<P>
Preparation work for choosing the model bases started in the
first half of 1996, he said, pointing out that the department has
selected the 100 sites after a comprehensive analysis of the
information and numerous consultations with various ministries and
departments.
</P>
<P>
"They are famous bases historically, have rich stores of
relics, and the work of the bases is effective," said the
official, explaining the standards for choosing the outstanding
bases.
</P>
<P>
Every province, autonomous region or municipality has at least
one model base, among which are museums, cemeteries, historical
sites and old residences, which reflect all aspects of China's
long history.
</P>
<P>
"Local governments at all levels should pay attention to and
support the establishment of the model bases," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
