<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Official Calls for Common Ideal, Belief in Building Socialism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- A high-ranking Chinese official
today urged young experts to do their best to understand China's
actual conditions, strengthen the common ideal in building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, and strive to propel the
country's opening-up and modernization into the next century.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau
and member of the Secretariat of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee, made the remark here during a meeting
with 29 young experts who have recently conducted research into
national conditions.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was sponsored by the Organization Department of the
CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Hu said he fully approved of their study, and hopes China's
young intellectuals will shoulder the historical responsibility of
leading the country's socialist modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Following Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics so as to revitalize the Chinese nation is
a job for the whole Party and the nation, Hu pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Hu stressed that the CPC is the core force of leading the
entire Chinese people in the cause of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
One of the most outstanding aspects of China at present is that
it is still, and will be for a long time, in the early stages of
socialism, Hu said, urging young intellectuals and experts to
study actual social conditions, and to mix with workers and
peasants so that all can work together for the country's socialist
development.
</P>
<P>
Hu called on young intellectuals and experts to turn their
patriotism into actual deeds, by contributing their knowledge and
expertise to China's modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
He noted that 20 years ago Deng Xiaoping put forward the idea
of respecting knowledge and special personnel, and the idea is
especially important now if China's lofty cross-century goals are
to be accomplished.
</P>
<P>
He urged authorities at all levels to continue to implement the
policy of respecting knowledge and special personnel.  
</P>
</TEXT>
