<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Meets Former German Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, and former German Foreign Minister Hans-Dietrich
Genscher have both expressed hope that relations between the two
countries will grow further.
</P>
<P>
Genscher told Li at their meeting here today that maintaining
good relations with China is an unchangeable point of Germany's
foreign policy. He believed the relations would be improved and
expanded in the coming century.
</P>
<P>
Li said the current relationship is very good. He hoped
politicians from both sides would continue to make common efforts
to promote the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Li also met with Antje Vollmer, vice-president of
the Bundestag, the lower house of the German parliament.
</P>
<P>
Vollmer said China has made remarkable achievements in
economic reform and in the opening-up drive. She said Germany was
following the development in China from a friends' point of view.
</P>
<P>
Late Tuesday, Li also met Michael Glos, vice-chairman of the
parliamentary group of German Chancellor Helmut Kohl's Christian
Democratic Union and its Bavarian sister party, the Christian
Social Union (CSU).
</P>
<P>
Stressing the importance of relations between Germany and
China, Glos said Germany hopes to improve the bilateral ties in a
sincere and good atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
Li told Glos that his meetings with German leaders over the
past few days had improved mutual understanding and relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Both being major countries of the world, China and Germany
should expand contacts and cooperation, Li said. 
</P>
