<HEADLINE> Jailbreak Attempt Kills 1, Injures 37 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 11 (Xinhua) -- A prisoner was killed and 37
others, including prisoners and policemen, were injured when
police opened fire to foil a jailbreak attempt in India's Assam
state on Tuesday, Press Trust of India reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, 350 prisoners attempted to escape
from the Karbi Anglong district jail in Assam around Tuesday noon,
breaking the inner prison gate with a truck.
</P>
<P>
Police was forced to resort to firing, resulting the death of a
prisoner who was convicted for drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The injured included 30 prisoners, two of whom received bullet
injuries. The remaining were policemen. No prisoners could escape
from the jail as they were caught and returned to their cells.
</P>
<P>
Additional forces were deployed in the jail in the northeastern
Indian state and the situation was reportedly under control.
</P>
</TEXT>
