<HEADLINE> Soldiers, Officers Urged to Study Deng's Thoughts on Army Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- All the soldiers and officers of
the People's Liberation Army (PLA) should carefully study the
"Outlines of Deng Xiaoping's Ideas on Building the Army in the New
Period," a senior Chinese official said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a forum held in Beijing to mark the publication of
the pamphlet, Liu Huaqing, vice-chairman of the Central Military
Commission, said that it is good supplementary material for the
study of Deng's ideas on building the Army in the new period.
</P>
<P>
The outline is not only true to Deng's works, but also explains
the major speeches of President Jiang Zemin on military affairs
and the major decisions of the Central Military Commission, added
Liu, who is also a Standing Committee member of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC).
</P>
<P>
He said that the pamphlet will play an important role in
encouraging the army to learn Deng's ideas and improving the
political work in the army.
</P>
<P>
"Deng's ideas on building the army in the new period are an
essential part of his theory on building socialism with Chinese
characteristics," he said.
</P>
<P>
Soldiers and officers should put the theory to practice in this
important time to help build up both the country and the army, Liu
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that when doing the study, people should spend more
time reading Deng's original works.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers and officers should combine this task with the
study and implementation of the major decisions on army building
and national defense, issued by the CPC Central Committee, with
Jiang at the core, and the Central Military Commission, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
The "Outlines," compiled by the General Political Department of
the PLA with the approval of the Central Military Commission, has
been officially dispatched to the whole army. 
</P>
</TEXT>
