<DOCNO> XIE19970611.0028 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malt Factory Produces Enough to Supply Breweries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The general manager of the
Assela Malt factory, Getahun Kassaye said today his factory has
now reached a stage whereby it could fully supply quality malt to
the breweries in Ethiopia, according to a report from the
Ethiopian News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The Assela malt factory now produces 15,000 tons of malt
yearly, compared with only 10,000 tons in the past. The factory
obtained a net profit of 3.4 million birr (about 500,000 U.S.
dollars) from the sale of 9,000 tons of malt over the past nine
months of the current fiscal year (July 8, 1996- July 7, 1997).
</P>
<P>
The general manager attributed to the boost in production to
the installation of additional pitchers and other equipment at a
cost of 26 million birr (about 3.8 million U.S. dollars) and
farmers supplying adequate barley to the factory.
</P>
<P>
He said the factory could supply local breweries quality malt
according to their demands.
</P>
<P>
He added that as the quality of beer depends upon the quality
of barley the factory is now engaged in distributing select-seed
to peasants in the area of credit basis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
