<HEADLINE> Premier Congratulates Successful Satellite Launching </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XICHANG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The successful launching of two
satellites in one month will have a great bearing on China's
status in the international aerospace arena, Chinese Premier Li
Peng said today in this southwest China city.
</P>
<P>
The premier made the comment today in Xichang, Sichuan
province, during a meeting with personnel who participated in the
successful launching of a meteorological satellite yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Li, on behalf of the Communist Party of China Central Committee
and the State Council, congratulated the China Aerospace Corp.,
the Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for National
Defense, and all those who were involved in the development and
launching of the Fengyun 2 satellite.
</P>
<P>
By now, the Fengyun 2 meteorological satellite has entered the
earth's quasi-synchronous orbit.
</P>
<P>
"The successful launching of the Dongfanghong 3 and the Fengyun
2 satellites in less than one month is of both great economic and
political significance," the premier noted.
</P>
<P>
He called the launchings "a generous gift to Hong Kong's return
by all the aerospace scientists and workers."
</P>
<P>
The premier said that since China sent its first satellite into
orbit at the beginning of the 1970s, China's aerospace industry
has made great achievements that attract worldwide attention, and
this has helped China obtain a status befitting such a great
country.
</P>
<P>
He urged the industry to learn from both the successes and
failures of the past to make progress in the future.  
</P>
