<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Denies Rumored Mirage Sale to Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 11 (Xinhua) -- France today denied a report by a
Taiwan newspaper that the Socialist government wishes to sell 60
Mirage 2000-5 combat aircraft to Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"This report does not tell the truth," said French Foreign
Ministry spokesman Jacques Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
He said France respects "word by word" the 1994 Franco-Chinese
agreement, in which Paris promised not to sell armaments to Taiwan
from then on.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman noted that the agreement paved the way for the
normalization of bilateral relations, which had been shaken by the
decision of a former French government to sell 60 Mirage combat
aircraft to Taiwan in 1993.
</P>
<P>
During his state visit in China in May, President Jacques
Chirac reaffirmed France's commitment to not sell armaments to
Taiwan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
