<HEADLINE> President: Iran Seeks Closer Ties With ASEAN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani said here today Iran has given special priority to its
relations with member states of the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani made the remarks in a meeting with Thai Parliament
Speaker Wan Mohammad Noor Matha.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian president said that the growing cooperation
among Asian developing states, proper conditions in the region
and the rich resources and abundant raw materials will turn Asia
into the largest economic pole in next century.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani also welcomed formation of parliamentary friendship
groups between Iran and Thailand. He said that there exist
wide-range of areas for bilateral cooperation and joint
investment in oil, gas, petrochemical and fishery sectors.
</P>
<P>
Noor Matha said Thailand attached importance to its relations
with Iran.
</P>
<P>
He described his talks with Iranian government officials here
as useful and expressed the hope that trade relations would
further develop between Bangkok and Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Noor Matha said that Iran enjoys rich oil and gas resources,
adding that joint investment with Iran is to the benefit of all
countries.
</P>
<P>
Prior to his departure, he told reporters that through joint
investment in the areas of oil and gas, Iran and Thailand will
be able to meet their oil needs and to export the surplus.
</P>
<P>
Matha, who arrived here Monday for a three-day visit, stressed
that formation of the two countries parliamentary friendship
group has been the greatest achievement of his visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
