<HEADLINE> NPC Begins Inspection Tour Of Law On Product Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Governments and people's
congresses at all levels should strengthen the enforcement of the
law on Product Quality, said Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
Wang made the remarks here today after hearing a report on the
enforcement of the law from the provincial government of south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Four inspection teams sent by the Standing Committee of the NPC
have gone to provinces of Guangdong, Zhejiang, Hebei and Henan,
while Tianjin Municipality, Liaoning, Shaanxi, Yunnan and Fujiang
provinces have begun conducting self-inspections on their
effectiveness in carrying out the law.
</P>
<P>
Governments and enterprises at all levels should emphasize
product quality, as it is crucial for enterprises that want to get
a foothold in the international market, said Wang Guangying.
</P>
<P>
A leader in China's reform and opening drive, Guangdong has the
fastest growing economy in the country, but in some parts of the
province, shoddy or fake products still are sold.
</P>
<P>
As many as 5,150 stores that sell poor-quality products have
been punished in Guangdong since 1994, and more than 760 workshops
which produce phony goods have been closed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
