<HEADLINE> Kenya's Tea Exports Hit 333 M. U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Kenya earned 18 billion Shillings
(about 333 million U.S. Dollars) from tea exports last year,
making the country the largest tea exporter in the world, the
East African Standard newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The total of Kenya's tea earnings stood at 20 billion
Shillings (370 million Dollars) in 1996, said a report from the
Ministry of Agriculture, Livestock Development and Marketing.
</P>
<P>
The local tea market only accounted for two billion Shillings
(37 million Dollars), said the report.
</P>
<P>
The tea production jumped to 257,162 tons in the eastern
African country last year, up 5.2 percent from recorded 244,000
tons in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The increase was due to favorable weather conditions, timely
application of fertilizer and the improved prices.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, production of cashew nut has fallen by nearly 60
percent in the country over the past four years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
