<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
decline sharply on the Singapore market with the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials Index down 21.29 points to close below the
2000-point psychological resistance level at 1993.49 points today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume dropped to 100.69 million units, valued at
282.71 million Singapore dollars (about 197.7 million US dollars).
Declines overwhelmed advances by 201 to 95, while 328 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
HuanHsin was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 12.47 million units. It was followed by the Hong Kong
Land which had eight million shares traded. The DBS (Development
Bank of Singapore) Land was next with 3.69 million shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
The Bukit Sembawang, Elec, and the Singapore Press Holdings
(SPH) Foreign shared the top spot on the gainers' list as each of
them rose by 20 cents to finish at 28.2 Singapore dollars, 5.9 US
dollars and 29.2 Singapore dollars respectively. Osprey and the
Thai Prime Fund increased by 15 cents to end at 2.72 Singapore
dollars and nine US dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it
declined by 1.5 Singapore dollars to close at 22.7 dollars.
Cerebos fell by 1.25 dollars to end at 6.75 dollars, while Samanda
Holdings finished 60 cents lower at 11.4 Singapore dollars.
</P>
