Hong Kong and fly home to different provinces in the Chinese
inland areas on July 1, according to the Regional Council (RC).
</P>
<P>
The pigeons will be brought to Hong Kong from the Chinese
inland areas on June 29 purposely for the 100,000 Homing Pigeons
Releasing Ceremony jointly organized by the RC, the State Physical
Culture and Sports Commission of China and the Chinese Racing
Pigeon Association.
</P>
<P>
Announcing this today, Adolf Hsu, director of the Regional
Services Department, said that the ceremony is held to mark the
return of Hong Kong to China, noting that the pigeons'
return to their homeland would symbolize Hong Kong's return to her
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Hsu said that the event will start at 11:30 a.m. on July 1 at
Sha Tin Sports Ground with a bustle of performances by popular
singers, children's choir and Chinese dances, followed by the
climax of the day -- the release of homing pigeons.
</P>
<P>
The 100,000 Homing Pigeons Releasing Ceremony is among the many
cultural, recreational and sports activities either organized by
the RC on its own or jointly organized with other groups to share
the joy of Hong Kong's return to her motherland with
residents. 
