<HEADLINE> Five S. Leonean Soldiers Executed for Looting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The military authorities in Sierra
Leone executed five soldiers for looting on Tuesday, local media
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said this indicated that the coup leaders have
started taking tough actions against looting and raping, which
has been wild in Freetown since the May 25 coup.
</P>
<P>
Four of the soldiers were executed for trying to loot and rape
nuns at a convent in Freetown, while the fifth for killing a
photographer to get his camera, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The ruling Armed Forces Revolutionary Council also appealed to
the public to report any soldier found looting or any armed
robbery case to the police.
</P>
<P>
The authorities also ordered the arrest of over 700 prisoners
set free from a Freetown prison during the coup. They suspected
that the prisoners were behind the looting and robbery cases.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Freetown indicated that there have been a wide
spread of lootings after the coup. Among the victims are foreign
nationals and international organizations.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank of Sierra Leone was also looted and razed.
About 800 million Leone (nearly one million U.S. Dollars) was
reportedly carted away by the robbers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
