<HEADLINE> Volkeswagen Sales Up 9.2 Percent Through May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The German carmaker Volkeswagen sold
about 1.8 million vehicles through May this year, an increase of
9.2 percent over the first five months of 1996, the company said
today.
</P>
<P>
Company chairman Ferdinand Piech told a meeting of company
employees in Wolfsburg that the sales in western Europe, however,
dropped by 0.5 percent to 595,000 cars, due to a 10.8 percent
decline in domestic sales.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the reduced sales in Germany to the upcoming
introduction of a new Golf car, the company's best-selling
model. Orders of the old models would drop as customers usually
awaited the new ones to appear on the market, he added.
</P>
<P>
But Piech noted that the Wolfsburg-based firm remained
Germany's leading carmaker with a 17.8 percent share of the
domestic market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
