<HEADLINE> Senior CPPCC Officials Hold Forum on Hong Kong's Return (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- To resolve the Hong Kong question
in accordance with the "one country, two systems" principle will
set a good example for the reunification of the motherland and act
as pioneering work for the peaceful settlement of issues between
countries left over from history.
</P>
<P>
The remark was made here today at a forum by some members of
the Subcommittee of Foreign Affairs under the National Committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
Yu Hongliang, a member of the subcommittee, said at the forum
that China's resumption of exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong
is of great significance for the reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is part of China's territory, but has been occupied
by Britain for more than 150 years. July 1 this year will be an
exciting day for all people of Chinese origin both at home and
abroad, and will be a great milestone in the course of the
motherland's reunification.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong to the embrace of the motherland will
be an example to greatly promote the resolution of the Macao issue
and Taiwan issue, he said.
</P>
<P>
From the aspects of economics, subcommittee member Jiang
Guanghua noted, Hong Kong's return will play an important role in
advancing the economic take-off of the Chinese nation. As an
international financial and trading center, Hong Kong for many
years has been making a remarkable contribution to the reform and
opening-up in the interior areas.
</P>
<P>
The great concept of "one country, two systems" is becoming a
great reality, and it will provide great experience with rich
contents, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Guanghua expressed his belief that after Hong Kong's
return on July 1, the central government will give fuller scope to
its unique function.
</P>
</TEXT>
