<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Have Brighter Future: Malaysian Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will achieve faster
development and its future will be brighter with support of the
inland areas of China after its return to China on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The view was expressed by Malaysia-China Friendship Association
President Usman Awang in a recent exclusive interview with Xinhua
here.
</P>
<P>
Usman Awang said "nowadays, China's position is strong. With
China as its backing and with its development linked with that in
China, Hong Kong, after its return to China, would be able to make
greater progress and would be better developed."
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's position as an international financial and trade
center will not only remain but also be further enhanced," he
said.
</P>
<P>
In the Asia-Pacific region, Hong Kong is playing an important
role in economic development, and besides, Hong Kong is China's
important gateway, therefore, Hong Kong to be more prosperous will
be "an inevitable outcome", he said.
</P>
<P>
He believed that Hong Kong will certainly become one of the
most prosperous and richest regions in the world and be one of the
world's very vital economic and financial centers.
</P>
<P>
The association president said some investors who earlier
transferred their investments from Hong Kong to some other places
in the world are now coming back to Hong Kong for investments.
This shows they are confident of Hong Kong to be economically
prosperous in the future.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong would continue to prosper because the Chinese
government has stipulated a series of practical principles and
policies for the region, including "one country, two systems",
which provide a guarantee for a stable and prosperous Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He believed that Hong Kong would succeed in implementing these
principles and policies.
</P>
<P>
He congratulated China on its resumption of the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong and congratulated the Hong Kong people
on their return to the embrace of the motherland.  
</P>
