light of Hong Kong's history and reality, and the international
situation as well.
</P>
<P>
Tang Longbin, who had participated in the signing of the
Sino-British Joint Declaration, said at today's forum that the
settlement of Hong Kong question was reached through arduous
efforts following 22 rounds of negotiations between China and
Britain.
</P>
<P>
The settlement of Hong Kong issue on the basis of "one country,
two systems" principle offers beneficial experience for the
international community to peacefully resolve questions left over
from history by means of negotiation, Tang noted.
</P>
<P>
Subcommittee member Wen Yezhan said that China's economic
growth and the increase of its national strength is the basis for
the smooth resumption of its exercise of sovereignty over Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
