<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Down as US Dollar Slides Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended lower
today against the US dollar, pressured by a sharp decline in the
greenback's exchange rate against the Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The falling US dollar/yen rate had pushed the Australian dollar
to a 10-month low against the yen before some of that weakness
flowed through to the Australian dollar/US rate.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the US dollar fell against the yen in the Asian
time zone as profit takers moved in after the release today of
Japanese current account data, which were in line with
expectations.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed lower at 75.98 US cents compared
to its previous session close at 76.13 US cents.
</P>
<P>
Against the yen, it closed at 84.32 yen, down from 86.08 yen
previously.
</P>
<P>
The Australian unit was last seen at these levels against the
yen in August 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended at 1.3011 German marks, from 1.3012
marks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
