<DOCNO> XIE19970611.0095 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebels' Death toll Rises to 210 in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Death toll of Tamil rebels rose to
210 by Tuesday when the rebels launched a massive attack on
military defense positions at Vavuniya in the Northern province,
according to a military spokesman here today.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,000 rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam
(LTTE) had taken part in the attack at Thandikulam and
Nochchimoddai in Vavuniya area and they attempted to destroy the
military headquarters with heavy artillery in a six hour battle.
</P>
<P>
However, the government troops finally repulsed the attack, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He said so far 210 rebels have been killed and over 300 others
injured while 58 dead bodies of soldiers have been recovered in
the fighting and 12 officers and 86 others wounded have been sent
to hospital.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the rebels' attack had been to destroy the army
headquarters to disrupt the ongoing military operation by the
government troops in the north of the country.
</P>
<P>
The troops has launched a major offensive code-named "Jaya
Sikuru' (Sure of Victory) since May 13 with the intention of
recapturing 75 kilometers of roadway on the main highway from
Vavuniya to Jaffna through the rebel-held territory.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a guerrilla war for a
separate state in the north and east of the country since 1983.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
