<DOCNO> XIE19970611.0096 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Publishes Complete Works of Qi Baishi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Hunan Fine Arts Publishing House
has published a 10-volume "Complete Works of Qi Baishi" to mark
the 40th anniversary of the passing away of country's best known
Chinese ink painter.
</P>
<P>
Qi Baishi, born into a farmer's family in Xiangtan, Hunan
Province in 1864, died in 1957 at the age of 93 in Beijing. He is
famous for his paintings of flowers, shrimps, fish and birds.
</P>
<P>
The complete works record his achievements by collecting 4,252
examples of his works and 500,000-characters of his poems and
articles.
</P>
<P>
The books also feature an index of Qi's works, give information
on their current location, year of production and lists the titles
of research papers on the artistic giant.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
