<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Electronic Industry Keeps in Express Track </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- China's electronic industry in the
first four months registered a 28.8 percent increase in output
value over the same period last year, according to latest
statistics from the country's Ministry of Electronic Industry
(MEI).
</P>
<P>
The industry's output value amounted to 104.1 billion yuan
during that period.
</P>
<P>
Profits made and taxes paid by the industry in the first
quarter reached 1.99 billion yuan, a rise of 32 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the output value of non-consumer electronic
products, such as program-controlled switchboards and computers,
posted an increase of 26.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
That of of consumer electronic products, such as color TV
sets and VCD (video compact disk) players, was up by 35.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The output value of electronic parts and components, including
integrated circuits, increased 23.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The production-to-sales ratio of electronic products improved
in the period. Major products, such as program-controlled
switches, personal computers and color TV sets all posted
remarkable growth.
</P>
<P>
China in the first four months produced switchboards with a
total of 3.96 million lines, 250,000 personal computers and 7.76
million color TV sets. Both the production and sales of personal
computers doubled in the period.
</P>
<P>
Also, according to statistics from China's General
Administration of Customs, imports and exports of electronic
products topped 9.08 billion US dollars in the first quarter, of
which exports were valued at 5.06 billion dollars, up 21.3
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
