<HEADLINE> Foreign Material Handling Equipment Showcased </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The First China International
Material Handling and Logistic Equipment Exhibition opened here
today.
</P>
<P>
Attending the exhibition are nearly 100 logistic facility
suppliers from Japan, US, Italy, Germany, Switzerland, Germany,
Singapore and China.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, which is a part of the ongoing 97' Asia and
Pacific Material Handling Conference, is jointly sponsored by
China's State Economic and Trade Commission (SETC), the Ministry
of Internal Trade, and the European Federation of Material Handling
Manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, a SETC leading official said
that to upgrade the infrastructure and technical benchmark for
material handling, the Chinese government invested 110 billion
yuan (about 13 billion US dollars) in the sector during the Eighth
Five-Year Plan period (1991-1995), a five fold increase over
investment during the previous five-year plan.
</P>
<P>
During the 1996-2000 period, China will focus on developing
industrial cranes, special transportation equipment, and material
handling machines, while importing more advanced logistic equipment.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony of was attended by Xu Penghang, executive
vice minister of SETC, Ma Yimin, chairman of China Association for
Material Handling, and Kurt Meier, secretary general of European
Federation of Material Handling Manufacturers, and senior
officials of concerned ministries.  
