<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Exports Up by 3.4 Percent in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's exports in May this
year amounted to 707 million U.S. dollars, showing an increase of
3.4 percent against the exports of 684 million dollars recorded in
April, the Federal Bureau of Statistics (FBS) said here today.
</P>
<P>
Imports in May increased by just 0.1 percent to 961 million
dollars as compared to the imports in April which totaled 960
million dollars, it said.
</P>
<P>
Main items of exports in May were cotton yarn, cotton fabrics,
readymade garments, knitwear, carpets and leather.
</P>
<P>
Main items of imports in May were petroleum products, power
generating machine road motor vehicles, Petroleum crude,
electrical machinery and apparatus.
</P>
<P>
Based on the above provisional figures of imports and exports,
Pakistan registered a trade deficit of 254 million dollars in May,
the FBS said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
