<HEADLINE> Kabila Wishes to Develop Good Relations with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KINSHASA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- President of the Democratic
Republic of Congo (DRCongo) Laurent-Desire Kabila said Tuesday
China is DRCongo's good friend and the two countries should
develop good relations on the basis of mutual benefit and equality.
</P>
<P>
During a 45-minute meeting with Chinese ambassador to DRCongo
Huang Shejiao, Kabila expressed "ardent desire" of his government
to consolidate and develop friendly relations with China.
</P>
<P>
Kabila said although great changes have taken place in both
DRCongo and China over the past 30 years, China has always been a
good friend of the Congolese people.
</P>
<P>
He praised China for persisting in its principles in
international affairs, saying that DRCongo expects to cooperate
with China in all fields.
</P>
<P>
Kabila said that China is welcomed to participate in DRCongo's
reconstruction programs, including agricultural development and
rehabilitation of roads and communication infrastructures.
</P>
<P>
Huang said the Chinese government hopes that DRCongo would
achieve great success in its reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government respects the choice of the Congolese
people. In safeguarding the national sovereignty and in the
construction of their respective countries, the people of China
and Congo have always provided each other with sympathy and
support," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the two countries have cooperated successfully in
economy and technology on the basis of mutual benefit and
equality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
