<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing to Attract More Investors by Opening Wider: New Mayor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing's newly-elected mayor
Pu Haiqing has vowed to establish a good image of an open
Chongqing and attract more overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Pu, who was elected mayor of Chongqing, the fourth municipality
of China, yesterday at the ongoing first session of the Chongqing
Municipal People's Congress, said Local people must build
Chongqing into a fully-open city which should cater to the needs
of other parts of China and the world in its economic development.
</P>
<P>
"Without opening wider and faster development," said the new
mayor, "we cannot attain the goal of enabling local residents live
a prosperous life".
</P>
<P>
Pu, 56, also pledged that Chongqing would be active in
participating in international division of labor and competition,
and in entering domestic and international macro-economic cycling.
</P>
<P>
According to Pu, a new opening pattern will be formed, with
downtown areas as the center, supported by the opening of
national-level economic and technological development zones and
high-tech industrial development zones, as well as the development
of areas along the municipality's expressways and the Yangtze
River.
</P>
<P>
Attracting and using overseas funds will be treated as a
priority of Chongqing's opening drive, said the mayor. He set the
goal for the use of overseas funds at four billion U.S. dollars
during the Ninth Five-Year-Plan Period (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of this year, Chongqing signed 108
contracts involving use of overseas funds. During the period, the
city actually brought in 170 million U.S. dollars in overseas
funds, a rise of 23.1 percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, the city had set up 2,560 overseas-backed
enterprises, involving 2.81 billion U.S. dollars in overseas funds
in real terms.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing will increase the sector range making use of overseas
investment, improve efficiency in using overseas funds and
increase guidance over the flow of foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile it will start joint ventures or cooperative
businesses with the world's first-rate companies by offering some
profitable projects and selecting key local enterprises for such
partnerships, said the mayor.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing has received 173 overseas delegations looking for
investment opportunities since it became China's fourth
municipality on March 14 this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
