<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 40 Percent of Ugandans to Die Before 40 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Almost up to 39 percent of
Ugandans are not expected to survive the age 40, reported the
local daily the Monitor today.
</P>
<P>
A report on 1997 human development to be launched by the
United Nations Development Program soon in Bonn, Germany was
quoted as saying that 50 percent of Ugandans earn less than one
U.S. Dollars a day while 51 percent of Ugandans have no access to
health services and 38.2 percent of adults are illiterate.
</P>
<P>
Sixty-two percent of Ugandans have no access to safe water,
according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Uganda is ranked by the report at the 53rd place out of 78
developing countries in the world with a HPI (human poverty
index) of 41.3 percent of its population.
</P>
<P>
HPI considers poverty in terms of "short lives, illiteracy and
lack of basic services". 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
