which came to power last March by forming a ruling coalition with
the participation of the Communist Party of Nepal (United Marxist
Leninist, CPN-UML).
</P>
<P>
The opposition in the country has alleged that workers of the
CPN-UML, the biggest party of the ruling coalition, resorted to
widespread illegal activities including threat, intimidation and
rigging to secure a landslide victory in the local polls.
