<HEADLINE> Turkish President Hails Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel
said here today that Hong Kong's return to China on July 1 under
the "one country, two systems" policy is of great significance to
the world.
</P>
<P>
Demirel said this while meeting a delegation from the Chinese
National People's Congress (NPC), which arrived here on June 5 for
a week-long goodwill visit.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish president said that as a world financial and trade
center, a stable and prosperous Hong Kong would be important for
the Turkish-Chinese trade as well as the world trade.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the Taiwan issue, Demirel said that his country
recognizes the People's Republic of China as the sole legitimate
government of China, stressing that Turkey and China should increase
high-level exchanges to enhance friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Zhou Jue, Vice Chairman of the NPC Foreign Affairs
Committee and delegation head, said that China has also attached
great importance to the Sino-Turkish relations, and hoped for
strengthened cooperation. 
