<HEADLINE> IAAF Denies Slaney and Farmer-Patrick Compete </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The IAAF, track and field's world
governing body, Tuesday threatened to suspend any athletes who run
against Mary Slaney or Sandra Farmer-Patrick if they compete in
the U.S. national championships.
</P>
<P>
The IAAF said that Slaney and Farmer-Patrick remain under
suspension and cannot run in the U.S. nationals starting Wednesday
in Indianapolis.
</P>
<P>
The IAAF reiterated its decision, announced May 31, to suspend
the two athletes until USA Track and Field holds a hearing into
their alleged positive drug tests.
</P>
<P>
IAAF general secretary Istvan Gyulai had sent official
notification Monday or Tuesday to Pat Rico, the president of
USATF, IAAF spokesman Giorgio Reineri said.  
</P>
