<HEADLINE> Mexico Backs China's Opposition to Foreign Interference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo
said today that Mexico opposes any foreign attempt to interfere in
China's internal affairs and will give invariable support to China
in its fight against outside pressure on its domestic policy.
</P>
<P>
"Mexico takes an unwavering stance on this issue -- China's
domestic affairs should be decided by the Chinese government and
the Chinese people," Zedillo told visiting Chinese parliamentary
officials at the presidential residence.
</P>
<P>
Zedillo welcomed the visit by the Chinese parliamentary
delegation, led by Buhe, Vice-Chairman of the Standing Committee
of China's National People's Congress (NPC), saying it would
further boost the parliamentary cooperation between the two
countries and contribute to closer bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Hailing China's fast growth in recent years, Zedillo said his
country will do its most to develop trade links with China and
encourage investment exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Buhe thanked the Mexican government for its support in China's
bid for re-entry into the World Trade Organization and on issues
of Taiwan, Tibet and human rights.
</P>
<P>
He said he is optimistic about the prospect for better
political and economic cooperations between the two countries.
