<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition in Warsaw Marks Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, June 10 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition on Hong Kong's return
to the motherland opened here today, reflecting the region's past
and present through 100 carefully chosen photographs.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, sponsored by the Chinese embassy to celebrate
the return, the history of the British occupation of Hong Kong and
the British invasion of China, the struggle by the Chinese
government and people to resume the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong under the "one country, two systems" principle initiated
by Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony at the Warsaw Independence
Museum, Chen Shize, the Chinese ambassador to Poland, told an
audience of about 200 local officials and residents that the
return of Hong Kong has been realized thanks to China's growing
strength.
</P>
<P>
He said that as a new era in Hong Kong is ushered in, its
status as an international center for finance, free trade and
transport and a better life for its residents is guaranteed.
</P>
<P>
A documentary film on Hong Kong's history over the past century
was also shown at the exhibition which runs for one month. 
</P>
