BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin will attend
the handover ceremony on the transfer of power of Hong Kong at the
head of the Chinese Government Delegation, at the midnight of June
30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony for the transfer of power of Hong Kong will be
held in the hall on the Fifth Floor of the New Building of the
Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee and chairman of the Central Military
Commission, will go to Hong Kong and attend the ceremony for the
transfer of power of Hong Kong to be jointly held by the
governments of China and Britain.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, at the head of the central delegation, Jiang will
attend the ceremony for the establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) and inauguration of the Hong Kong SAR
government.
</P>
<P>
Members of the delegation include Premier Li Peng and
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen; Wang Hanbin, vice-chairman of the
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee; Zhang
Wannian, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission; Wu
