<DOCNO> XIE19970611.0149 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Three Projects in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today approved a
financing of 37.1 million U.S. dollars for three projects in
Africa.
</P>
<P>
A loan of 10 million dollar equivalent will be used to back
Gabon's privatization and regulatory capacity building project.
The project will help increase the level of private sector
investment in Gabon.
</P>
<P>
A credit of 14.3 million dollars is earmarked for Guinea
Bissau's basic education support project. The project will help
the government achieve quality basic education through the
improvement of school facilities, the enhancement of the
teaching-learning process, the improvement of human resource
management in the Ministry of Education and the laying of the
institutional ground work for the next projects and a sector
policy framework.
</P>
<P>
Another credit of some 12.8 million dollars will finance
Zambia's environmental support program, which is designed to back
the Government's development strategy of poverty reduction within
the framework of economic growth and protection of the environment
and natural resources.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the World Bank also okayed a nine-million-dollar
credit to Moldova in support of a second private sector
development project.
</P>
<P>
All credits will be channeled through the International
Development Association, the concessionary lending arm of the
World Bank for developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
