<HEADLINE> China To Develop Bank IC Card Standards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBC)
and VISA International today signed a memorandum of understanding
on developing China's Bank Intelligent Card Standards.
</P>
<P>
"The standards provide regulations and measures for developing
the IC card industry in China, and a technical foundation for the
use of IC cards among industries and regions, as well as for the
sharing of infrastructure," said Chen Jing, Director of PBC's
Payment and Technology Department.
</P>
<P>
The standards will elaborate the basic function of intelligent
cards issued by domestic banks and ensure compatibility with
international IC card applications.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation will start this June, while the first version
of Bank IC Card Standards is scheduled to come out in December.
</P>
<P>
Chinese banks have more than one million IC cards in use.
</P>
