<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The General Office of the State
Council, China's highest governing body, announced here today that
the people across the country will have a day off on July 1 this
year to mark Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The notice says that the Chinese government will resume its
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1, which is a grand
historic occasion for the Chinese nation.
</P>
