<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 200 Rebels, Soldiers Killed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- About 200 Tamil rebels and
government soldiers Tuesday were killed when rebels of the
liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) launched a massive attack
on military defense positions at Vavuniya in the Northern Province
of Sri Lanka, according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
About 500 to 700 LTTE rebels stormed the military positions
with heavy artillery in a six hour battle. The military were
finally able to repulse the attack.
</P>
<P>
The reports said around 70 soldiers and 60 civilians were
killed and many others injured in the action while at least 60
rebels were killed and over 150 others wounded.
</P>
<P>
The rebels were able to cause heavy material losses. They blew
up an army ammunition dump that exploded when a mortar landed
during fierce fighting.
</P>
<P>
In addition, at least three armored fighting vehicles were
among the millions of rupees worth of armaments lost during
Tuesday's battle which is considered the biggest attack against
government troops by the LTTE so far this year.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels, having approached the defense from the western
flank of the main road, attempted to destroy the headquarters and
the artillery gun position in Vavuniya area. The aim of the LTTE
had been to destroy the headquarters to disrupt the ongoing
military operation by the troops in the north of the country.
</P>
<P>
On May 13, government forces launched a major offensive
code-named "Jaya Sikuru" (Certain Victory) with the intention of
capturing 75 kilometers of roadway on the main highway from
Vavuniya to Jaffna through the rebel-held territory.
</P>
<P>
To date, the forces have been able to recapture only 16
kilometers with rebel resistance building up as the troops inch
their way forward.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a war for a separate state in the
north and east of the country since 1983.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
