<HEADLINE> ADB Provides Nepal with Interest-free Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
has agreed to provide Nepal with an interest-free loan of 27
million U.S. dollars for its Tribhuvan International Airport
improvement project, sources here said today.
</P>
<P>
The improvement project will address the capacity, safety and
institutional issues at the Tribhuvan International Airport.
</P>
<P>
The loan will also be utilized for the capacity building of the
Civil Aviation Authority of Nepal (CAAN).
</P>
<P>
The ADB signed an agreement with Nepal in February to provide a
technical assistance of 500,000 U.S. dollars for the establishment
of CAAN as an autonomous entity to manage the civil aviation
sub-sector.
</P>
<P>
The ADB has been the main donor in the civil aviation sector of
Nepal.  
