<HEADLINE> Argentine President Meets Visiting Japanese Emperor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President Carlos
Menem today met visiting Japanese Emperor Akihito and Empress
Michiko and they expressed hopes for closer bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the royal couple at the presidential residence of El
Olivo, Menem said the relations between Argentina and Japan are
cordial in nearly a century of established ties.
</P>
<P>
Akihito, arriving Monday for a three-day visit, said his visit
would contribute to his deeper understanding of the enormous
development of the South American country in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Akihito, who visited Argentina 30 years ago as the crown
prince, is making the first royal visit to Latin America. The
couple had earlier visited Brazil and spent 10 days there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
