<HEADLINE> Brazil Beats England 1-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Romario's goal helped Brazil a 1-0
win over England on Tuesday in a match of the Tournoi de France.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Romario scored in the 61st minute to give
Brazilians their ninth win in 19 meetings with England, who was
already crowned champions here.
</P>
<P>
World footballer of the year Ronaldo was involved in the
action, putting the ball through to Leonardo, who had been looking
dangerous throughout the game.
</P>
<P>
Leonardo found Romario, back to his best after a World Cup hang
over which saw him gain weight and lack motivation, who steered
the ball past England keeper David Seaman with the outside of his
right boot.
</P>
<P>
Alan Shearer, England's leading scorer, complimented the
Brazilians on their goal but added that he felt the gap between
European teams and South Americans was narrowing. 
