<HEADLINE> Italy's GDP Target in 1997 Still Within Reach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Italian government's target of
1.2 percent gross domestic product (GDP) growth in 1997 is "still
within reach" despite slower growth reported for the first quarter
of the year.
</P>
<P>
Speaking before the Senate and Lower House budget committees
here today, Alberto Zuliani, chief of Italy's Statistics Bureau
(Istat), said that against the poor results in the first quarter
are signals that the economy is strengthening in the second
quarter due to an expected recovery of domestic demand buoyed by
greater consumer confidence.
</P>
<P>
The government's target of 1.2 percent in its economic
guidelines (now before parliament for review) was reachable but "a
very strong pace of growth will be needed in the upcoming months,"
he added. 
</P>
