<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances China's Poverty-Relief Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today offered
180 million U.S. dollars in financing for China's Qinba Mountains
poverty-relief project.
</P>
<P>
The project will promote multisectoral rural development,
increase labor mobility, and reverse environmental degradation in
the Qinba Mountains, located in northern China, as an effective
means to combat poverty and reduce the number of absolute poor.
</P>
<P>
It will also integrate a multisectoral program administered at
the central and provincial levels with local poverty reduction
initiatives.
</P>
<P>
The financing is composed of two parts, a loan of 30 million
dollars and a credit of 150 million dollars equivalent, which will
be channeled through the International Development Association,
the concessionary lending wing of the World Bank for developing
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
