<HEADLINE> Myanmar Strives to Advance Computer Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is making determined
efforts to advance its computer education in schools as a
strategy for modernization in the realm of information
technology, Myanmar Minister for National Planning and Economic
Development was quoted by today's official paper The New Light of
Myanmar as saying.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a technical seminar on information technology for
government organizations here Tuesday, Minister Brigadier-General
Abel disclosed that his country's Central Statistical Organization
is running a star network as the national computing backbone,
linking 14 government departments in his ministry and the Finance
and Revenue Ministry.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 applications, operational on mainframe and
microcomputers, covering the areas of statistical computing,
banking, insurance, customs, internal revenues and economic
planning, have been implemented and are in use since 1986, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, jointly sponsored by the Myanmar Ministry of
National Planning and Economic Development and the PT Astra
Graphia Group of Indonesia, included talks by Indonesian resource
persons on information technology with attendance of Myanmar
government officials and personnel of private computer companies.
 
</P>
