<HEADLINE> Ukrainian PM Meets Chinese Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine is full of confidence in
developing an all-round cooperation with China, Ukrainian Prime
Minister Pavel Lazarenko said during his meeting with visiting
Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian here today.
</P>
<P>
Trade between China and Ukraine has reached 846 million
U.S. dollars in 1996 and is expected to climb to one billion
dollars this year, he added.
</P>
<P>
He predicted the Ukrainian economy would stop slipping and
start to recover at the end of 1997. The prime minister said
Ukraine could control the decrease of its production within 9
percent in 1997, compared with 47 percent in 1995.
</P>
<P>
However, Ukraine has successfully curbed inflation, which stood
at 5.2 percent in the first five months this year, down from 37
percent in 1996 and 230 percent in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Lazarenko stressed it is a priority for Ukraine to develop
trade ties with China. He hoped that leaders of both countries
would make concerted efforts to lift bilateral relations to the
level of strategic partnership.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who arrived here on June 6 for a five-day visit, said that
military cooperation should go as fast as trade links between the
two countries. He emphasized that the cooperation between Beijing
and Kiev would contribute to regional and global stability.
