<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Passenger Car Sales Down in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The number of passenger cars sold
in the Philippines went down 5.8 percent in the first five months
this year to 33,912 units from last year's 35,995 units, local
press reported today.
</P>
<P>
In May alone, passenger car sales reached only 6,603 units,
10.2 percent lower than the 7,357 units the major local assemblers
sold for the same month last year, the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to the Chamber of Automotive Manufacturers of the
Philippines Inc., the decrease was due to a slowdown in bank
processing of car loans and the market anticipation of the
introduction of new car models.
</P>
<P>
Data released by the chamber also showed that sales of all top
four car brands reached only 4,870 units in May, 16.4 percent
lower than their year ago level of 5,829.
</P>
<P>
Honda remained the country's top car brand last month, but the
1,478 cars sold by Honda Cars Phils. Inc. represented a 25.2
percent drop from the 1,977 cars it sold for the same month last
year.
</P>
<P>
The sales figures of local car assemblers serve as a major
economic indicator. Economists use it to measure the growth of the
middle class. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970611.0182 </DOCNO>
