<HEADLINE> Venezuela Imports More Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's imports totalled 3.198
billion U.S. dollars in the first four months this year, up 23.3
percent over the same period last year, said the Central Bureau of
Statistics and Computer Database (OCEI).
</P>
<P>
In a report published today OCEI said the upsurge was reflected
in all the sectors with an emphasis on the import of
transportation materials that rose by 33.8 percent to 313 million
dollars, followed by electrical materials, which accumulated 1.2
billion dollars by a variation of 31 percent.
</P>
<P>
About 71.6 percent of the imports came from the United States,
Colombia, Germany, Brazil, Japan, Italy and France.
</P>
<P>
Japanese exports to the country soared by 41.6 percent to 126
million dollars, and Brazilian exports increased 40.4 percent to
160 million dollars between January and April of this year.
</P>
