<HEADLINE> Corolla Cars to March into Chinese Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Toyota Motor Corp is
introducing a new series of cars into the Chinese market, the
"China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The new Corolla cars, Toyota's global sales champion, are
making their debut at the seventh Shanghai International
Automotive Industry Fair which opens yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Corollas will be the stars of the fair, said Koji Hasegawa, a
Toyota director and board member.
</P>
<P>
The annual vehicle fair, a festival for thousands of Chinese
auto fans and a showcase for international and domestic auto
producers, is held alternately in Beijing and Shanghai cities.
</P>
<P>
General Motors, Ford, Mitsubishi, Volkswagen, Chrysler and
Hyundai are all represented at the auto show, which will run
through June 16.
</P>
<P>
Hasegawa said the new Corollas, equipped with 1.6-liter and
1.3-liter engines to meet China' market demands, will be in
showrooms this month. There will be six models available.
</P>
<P>
Although imported cars have not sold well in China during the
past couple of years and few believe a substantial pick-up will
appear this year, Hasegawa is "optimistic about the sales prospects
of the new cars,"
</P>
<P>
But he said that much work needs to be done in the Chinese
market before an accurate sales forecast for the new vehicles can
be drawn.
</P>
<P>
This is the eighth generation of Corollas since 1966.
</P>
<P>
The cars are now manufactured in 15 countries, Hasegawa said,
noting that cars sold to China will be made in Japan.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the fair are Toyota's new 1.3-liter 8A-FE
engine with its latest technology for environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Toyota invested in an engine project last May in Tianjin, with
a registered capital of 24.8 million US dollars. Its 24 component
joint ventures in China give the company a strong footing in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Hasegawa said Toyota plans to launch a passenger car project in
Tianjin with Chinese partners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
