<HEADLINE> Chinese Government Vows to Guarantee HK's Fresh Water Supply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government will
continue to ensure a fresh water supply to Hong Kong as it has
done for the last 32 years, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted vice-premier Jiang Chunyun as saying that
the move will help maintain the territory's booming economy and
prosperity after it returns to the motherland on July 1 of this
year.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called upon 1,500 project workers to contribute more to
welcome the handover by working hard and ensuring the fresh water
supply, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Today, more than 70 percent of Hong Kong's fresh water used by
its more than six million residents and industries depend on a
water supply project launched 32 years ago by the central
government, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three decades, the project has supplied nearly 10
billion cubic meters of fresh water to Hong Kong, the paper
added.  
</P>
