<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fossilized Birds Unearthed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archeologists have
unearthed 23 fossilized birds believed to be 150 million years old
in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Among them, 11 were discovered at a site in the city of
Baipiao, a treasure trove of primitive birds. So far, hundreds of
fossilized birds have been found in Liaoning, providing important
clues for scientists to study the origin and evolution of birds in
the Jurassic period.
</P>
<P>
The newly-found bird fossils were from the family of
Confuciusornis, similar to Sinosauropteryx, which some scientists
theorize is the ancestor of all modern birds.
</P>
<P>
The fossils were excavated in a five-meter-deep pit by a group
of scientists who were doing investigation work there.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970611.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suspected Bank Robbers Captured in Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rican police announced
today that they have arrested eight suspects of a bank robbery
gang and confiscated several weapons.
</P>
<P>
Three Costa Ricans, three Colombians, one Panamanian and one
Venezuelan were detained early Monday morning in different houses
outside San Jose, judicial investigative police authorities (OIJ)
said.
</P>
<P>
The gang has been operating for several months and is believed
to have committed at least five robberies.
</P>
<P>
Police did not disclose the names of those detained but pointed
out that the leader of the gang is a Colombian.
</P>
<P>
The weapons seized were an AK-47 assault rifle, a Uzi machine
gun, three revolvers and detonators for explosives.
</P>
<P>
An OIJ agent said the police were alarmed by the violence of
the group in robbing a branch of the National Bank in Cartago, a
city 25 kilometers southeast of San Jose.
</P>
<P>
According to the police, the gang was trying to seize money to
purchase weapons of higher caliber and plot bank robberies in
metropolitan and rural areas where banks are not well guarded.
</P>
</TEXT>
