<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Telecom Expanding in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- China Telecom (Hong Kong)'s
purchase of a 5.5 percent stake in Hong Kong Telecom from British
parent Cable and Wire (C and W) last Friday was purely a business
deal, China Telecom President Zhang Ligui said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Today's "China Daily" quoted Zhang as saying that the operation
will be conductive to long-term cooperation between China Telecom
and Hong Kong Telecom and continue Hong Kong Telecom's sustainable
development in the future.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that China will continue its efforts to develop
friendly ties with telecom firms from other countries and regions
and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
On June 6, Posts and Telecommunications Minister Wu Jichuan and
C and W Chief Executive Richard Brown sealed the agreement in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Under it, C and W will sell a 5.5 percent stake to China
Telecom (Hong Kong) for 9.177 billion Hong Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
The payment of the full amount will be in cash within 45 days
after the contract was signed, the paper says.  
</P>
</TEXT>
