<HEADLINE> Triple Honor for Hong Kong Footballer Au Wai-Lun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Au Wei-lun of Hong Kong's senior
soccer club of South China won the honors of Hong Kong's Player of
the Year, Top Footballer and Most Welcomed Footballer at a
ceremony on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time in the history of the local game that a
player won three top honors in a same season.
</P>
<P>
Au was first listed as one of the eleven Top Footballers of the
year and then elected Player of the Year through a poll by the
players, who were honored Tuesday, and the local media.
</P>
<P>
And the 25-year-old was also named as the Most Welcomed
Footballer as a result of a poll by local fans and the media.
</P>
<P>
South China, this season's senior League champion, won the
most honors as Au and six teammates were among the eleven Top
Footballers named.
</P>
<P>
Turning professional nine years ago, Au had played for two
other clubs before switching to South China four years ago.
</P>
<P>
A member of the Hong Kong team and usually assigned as a
forward or mid-fielder, Au is famed for his tricky play and sharp
shots. Having scored 18 goals so far this season, he is now
top-ranked among local Chinese players.
</P>
<P>
The annual selection was jointly organized by the Radio
Television Hong Kong, the Hong Kong Football Association and the
Hong Kong Chinese Football Association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
