<HEADLINE> US Says Russia Unlikely to Join Paris Club at G-8 Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Russia will not be able to join
the Paris Club at the Group of Seven summit in Denver on June
20-22, said local reports today.
</P>
<P>
A senior U.S. official, who declined to be named, was quoted as
saying that Russia is making progress in negotiations to join the
Paris Club but an agreement may not be reached in time.
</P>
<P>
"I would not be surprised if they could resolve these by next
week, but at this juncture I'm not counting on that happening,"
said the U.S. official.
</P>
<P>
At the summit with Russian President Boris Yeltsin in March,
U.S. President Bill Clinton agreed to accelerate the negotiations
for Moscow to join the club this year and Russia attended the G-7
summit fully.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Russia is also pressing for membership in a series
of institutions, that were once the exclusive preserve of the
West, including the Organization for Economic Cooperation and
Development and the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin will attend most of the meetings at the Denver summit,
which will gather leaders from the U.S., Canada, France, Britain,
Japan, Italy and Britain. 
</P>
