<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Dollar Continues Slipping Against Yen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar ended mostly
higher today on eased concern about a euro delay, but it fell for
the fourth day against the yen.
</P>
<P>
The dollar fell to an intraday low of 111.65 yen, its second
consecutive six-month low, before recovering a bit to settle at
112.25 yen in New York, down from 112.93 yen Monday. The dollar
cost 1.7185 marks, up from 1.7072. The pound cost 1.6385 U.S.
dollars, up from 1.6367 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Over four days the dollar has lost 4 yen or 3.4 percent against
the Japanese currency.
</P>
<P>
Other late-dollar rates in New York compared with late Monday:
1.4417 Swiss francs, up from 1.4388; 5.8060 French francs, up from
5.7675; 1,696.00 Italian lire, up from 1,687.50; 1.3873 Canadian
dollars, down from 1.3875. 
</P>
</TEXT>
