<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Funding for Rhino Conservation Poor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Two international animal rights
groups reported today here that funding for the conservation of
five species of the world's rhinoceros remains woefully
inadequate.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the wildlife trade monitoring programme of world
wide fund for nature and the world consevation union told a press
conference that the rhino was severely endangered.
</P>
<P>
The two organisations also unveiled a report during the
ongoing convention on international trade in endangered species
meeting which reviews responses of 32 select countries to a 1994
resolution on the conservation of rhinoceros.
</P>
<P>
The report says, "the shortfall in funding to support
conservation of the world's remaining 12,000 rhinoceroses is the
most serious finding." 
</P>
</TEXT>
