<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordanian King Leaves for Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan left here
this afternoon on his second European visit within this year for
discussions on peace and economic issues.
</P>
<P>
During the fortnight-long visit, Hussein will rally support for
resuming the stalled Palestinian-Israeli peace negotiations and
strive to foster closer economic relations with Europe, Radio
Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
The king, accompanied by Queen Noor and Prime Minister Abdul
Salam Majali, will visit Netherlands, France, Switzerland and the
United Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
France, a member of the Paris Club, decided to provide the
kingdom with 16 million U.S. dollars in aid at the end of last
month.
</P>
<P>
Some local reports said that the United States Jewish society
will use money by Swiss banks to permanently settle the 3
million-strong Palestinian refugees in Jordan. This issue is
likely to be picked up during the king's visit, local observers
said.
</P>
<P>
The UK has expressed its willingness to play a role in the
Middle East and wants Jordan's help in this regard. In return, it
would contribute to the kingdom in economic terms.
</P>
<P>
In March, the King paid his first visit to Europe this year
to seek more economic help. 
</P>
</TEXT>
