<HEADLINE> Kinshasa Threatens to Retaliate after Shelling Incident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KINSHASA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic Republic of Congo
(DRC) today issued a warning of retaliation against the Congo
Republic after a shell flying across the Congo River from
Brazzaville fell and exploded in Kinshasa Monday.
</P>
<P>
The shell hit the residence of the first councillor of the
Nigerian Embassy, but no one was hurt. Witnesses said the
explosion resulted in a crater of 50 centimeters wide in the
ground.
</P>
<P>
In a communique issued today, the Foreign Minister of the DRC
Bizima Karaha described the incident as "a deliberate action aimed
at violating our territory."
</P>
<P>
"The government holds the authors of the shelling responsible,
no matter from which side the shell came from. It warns the two
belligerent sides of the conflict in Congo that any repetition will
be considered an attack to the security and sovereignty (of DRC)"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that "appropriate measures will be taken to
retaliate". 
</P>
</TEXT>
