<HEADLINE> Lesotho Parties Condemn Premier for Forming New </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 10 (Xinhua)-- Leaders of political parties
in Lesotho today condemned as a coup in the decision by prime
minister Ntsu Mokhehle to form a new political party and continue
as head of government.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, they said Mokhehle and his ministers usurped
power, contrary to the Lesotho constitution and without the
mandate of the people.
</P>
<P>
They said Mokhehle should have resigned and asked king Letsie
III to dissolve parliament and called elections. They also called
on friendly countries to withdraw recognition of Mokhehle's
governemnt.
</P>
<P>
Mokhehle on Monday announced his new party would be called the
Lesotho Congress for Democracy. He also declared a handover of
government to his newly-formed party from the long-ruling
Basutholand Congress Party.
</P>
<P>
Mokhehle's cabinet ministers would all remain the same, having
made the jump to the new party along with their leader. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
