<HEADLINE> Jordan's Crown Prince to Visit Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Jordan's Crown Prince Hassan will
pay an official visit to Turkey Thursday amid increasing
tension incurred by Turkish military thrust into northern Iraq,
Jordan's official news agency Petra reported today.
</P>
<P>
The details of Hassan's visit has not been disclosed.
</P>
<P>
On May 27, Jordan officially called on Turkey to pull its
troops immediately out of northern Iraq, saying its thrust into
Iraq to fight Kurdish rebels was a violation of Iraqi
sovereignty and a threat to its territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
Continued Turkish military operations in Iraq would also
accelerate tension in the area, a Jordanian Foreign Ministry
spokesperson said.
</P>
<P>
About 50,000-strong Turkish troops moved into northern Iraq
on May 14 allegedly to fight rebels of the Kurdish Workers Party
(PKK) there.
</P>
<P>
Last year, King Hussein and Hassan paid separate visits
to Turkey to discuss ways to get water from Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
