<HEADLINE> Turkish President Vows to Respect China's Sovereignty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel
said here today that Turkey deems Xinjiang an unalienable part of
the territory of China.
</P>
<P>
Demirel made the remark while meeting a delegation from the
Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) at the presidential
palace.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Turkey would not interfere in the internal
affairs of China, adding that the minority nationalities living
in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region are Chinese citizens.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of Hong Kong, Demirel said that Hong Kong's return
to the motherland on July 1 under the "one country, two systems"
principle was of great significance for the world.
</P>
<P>
Describing Hong Kong as a world financial and trade center,
the Turkish president said that a stable and prosperous Hong Kong
would contribute to the Turkish-Chinese trade and the world trade
as well.
</P>
<P>
Demirel also said that his country would stick to its "one
China" policy, recognizing the People's Republic of China as the
sole legitimate government of China.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish leader emphasized that Turkey and China should
increase the exchange of high-level visits to enhance their
friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Jue, vice chairman of the NPC Foreign Affairs Committee
and head of the Chinese delegation, said that China attaches
great importance to the Sino-Turkish relations and hopes the
bilateral cooperation would further develop.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese NPC delegation arrived in Turkey on June 5 for a
one-week good-will visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
