<HEADLINE> Canadian Firm and Tanzania Sign Petroleum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A Canadian firm, Canop
International Resources Ventures, today signed a Petorleum
Production Sharing Agreement (PSA) with the government, bringing
to four the number of Candian petroleum exploration companies in
the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement issued here by the Canadian High
Commission in the country, Canop together with the other three
companies are expected to spend about 100 million US Dollars for
oil and gas exploration in the country within the next one to two
years.
</P>
<P>
The other companies are: Dublin International Petroleum Co.,
Ocelot Energy Inc. and Antrim Resources of Calgary.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed here by the Minister for Energy and
Minerals of Tanzania, Abdallah Kigoda on behalf of the
government, the Chairman of Canop Joe Clark on behalf of Canop
and the Managing Director for the Tanzania Petroleum Development
Corporation (TPDC) on behalf of his firm.
</P>
<P>
Speaking during the signing ceremony, Joe Clark said his
company was expecting to invest 20 million US Dollars in the
exploration program which will include seismic reprocessing and
Ecquisition as well as drilling several exploration wells.
</P>
