<HEADLINE> Hussein Calls for Arab Solidarity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Jordan's King Hussein today called
for Arab solidarity and keeping security and stability in the
Middle East region.
</P>
<P>
The king issued the call in his telephone conversations with
Syrian President Hafez al-Assad before he left here for a two-week
European visit.
</P>
<P>
He said that any country should not interfere with the
internal affairs of other countries and should respect the
sovereignty and unity of the lands in order to keep security and
stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
The king noted that all sides should enhance consultation and
dialogue to safeguard Arab solidarity.
</P>
