<HEADLINE> African Youth Body Commends Tanzania for Peace, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Pan African Youth
Movement (PYM) today commended Tanzania for maintaining peace and
stability in the country since its independence three decades
ago.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference here today, PYM Secretary
General Aly Diop said Tanzania was among very few countries in
Africa which have managed to maintain peace and unity, which he
said is an example that should be emulated by other countries.
</P>
<P>
He commended Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa for his
efforts in safeguarding peace, a pre-requisite for development of
any country.
</P>
<P>
However, Diop noted with concern that many other African
countries were trapped in wars and conflicts which he said are
"the No. 1 enemies of development."
</P>
<P>
Diop also appreciated Tanzania's efforts and role in the
development of the youth body.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Tanzanian Foreign Minister Jakaya Kikwete commended
the youth organization for evolving a new and dynamic platform in
line with the changing political, economic and social situation
in the world.
</P>
<P>
Kikwete said the changes in the youth body will help
consolidate democracy, peace, development and youth employment,
particularly by using the national youth council structure to
ensure non-partisan involvement of youth.
</P>
<P>
Diop, who arrived in the country two weeks ago for a visit,
left here for the PYM headquarters in Algeria. 
</P>
