<HEADLINE> Tanzania Hopes to Revive Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian Minister for
Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation, Jakaya Kikwete,
today expressed Tanzania's desire to revive economic cooperation
wtih the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Kikwete made the remarks after receiving credentials from the
Nairobi-based Charge de Affairs of the Czech Republic, Zdenek
Dobieas.
</P>
<P>
The republic of Czech was born in 1993 following the split of
the former Czechoslavakia into two republics Czech and Slovak.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued by the Tanzanian foreign
ministry, the minister said Tanzania, which used to have strong
relations with the former Czechoslovakia, was standing to gain a
lot from the republic's successful economic transformation drive
particularly the privatisation program.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Dobieas told Kikwete that the private sector in the
Czech Republic was contributing over 70 percent to the country's
Gross domestic Product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
He said his country was determined to revitablizing economic
relations with African countries, adding that the republic was
supporting small scale projects for poverty alleviation.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, a two-day working visit of Czech's
Deputy Foreign Minister Helena Bambosava, which was scheduled to
start today, has been postponed indefinately due to unexpected
political developments in the republic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
