<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt to Turn Famous Hangouts to Museums </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- As a way of developing cultural
heritage, Egypt will turn some of its celebrated historical sites
into outdoor museums, said an Egyptian archeological expert.
</P>
<P>
This issue was discussed at an international meeting held here
today on preserving historical heritage around Europe and the
Mediterranean, said Ali Hassan, Egyptian Higher Council of
Antiquities (HCA) Secretary General, who chaired the session.
</P>
<P>
"A number of distinguished places in Egypt will be chosen to be
turned into open-air museums," he added.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the "Museums Sans Frontiers" project committee
attended the meeting under the sponsorship of the International
Mediterranean Sea Lights Organization.
</P>
<P>
The project, funded by Spain and Austria, is taking place
within the Euro-Mediterranean partnership on developing
archeological, historical and cultural heritage for Mediterranean
countries.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, Egypt has almost 30 percent of the
globe's monuments and the government is eager to use them to get
on the international train of tourism investments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
