<HEADLINE> Minister Warns Against Deforestation in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Minister of
Agriculture Seifu Ketema today warned against the country's rapid
rate of deforestation which he said is 200,000 hectares annually.
</P>
<P>
"Ethiopia will entirely lose its forestry resources by the
year 2020 unless measures are taken to curb the practice," he
told a meeting on national forestry resources policy held here.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey, about 43 million hectares of land in
highland Ethiopia has suffered various forms of degradation,
rendering about 2 million hectares of land uncultivatable.
</P>
<P>
And Ethiopia loses about 200 million tons of soil to
neighboring countries annually while only 4 million hectares of
its land mass is currently covered with forest, said the
minister.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government has formulated a forestry and land
use policy with the view to controlling the depletion of the
nation's natural resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
