<HEADLINE> European Shares Mixed, London Hits Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Shares on Europe's major stock
markets mixed today, with London hitting a new high but Frankfurt
and Paris ending lower.
</P>
<P>
Shares on London market soared to a record peak, taking their
cue from a resumption of the strong rally on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE-100 index of British leading shares swept past the key
psychological resistance point of 4,700 to close up 52.9 points at
4,739.6, breaking the previous closing and intraday peaks set on
May 16. Trading volume was around 800 million shares.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, a more stable day on the currency markets helped
calm the German share market as the DAX index recouped early
losses to end the floor session little changed.
</P>
<P>
The 30-share DAX closed bourse trade down 2.42 points at
3,665.01, having dipped as low as 3,648.45 early in the session.
</P>
<P>
On Paris stock market, the CAC-40 index closed lower in
relatively light volume as investors took their cue from
uncertainty over the euro to book profits. Traders said the market
needed to consolidate after the surprise rise since the Socialist
election win. The CAC-40 index ended down 22.02 points at
2,664.18. 
