<DOCNO> XIE19970611.0271 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Surpasses 7,500 Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
closed above 7,500 points for the first time today as stocks
staged another record-setting advance despite a weak day in the
technology sector and the bond market.
</P>
<P>
The Dow nearly surrendered a 94-point gain in the morning, but
spiked higher over the last hour of trading, rising by 60.77
points to 7,539.27 and setting its third straight record high.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a 6-to-5 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, with its volume climbing to 526.98 million
shares from 465.58 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 2.36 to 865.27, and
the NYSE's composite index rose 1.59 to 451.76. It was the third
record close in a row for both measures.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange composite index rose 1.54 to 621.11,
setting its second straight high after a year-long drought.
</P>
<P>
But the Nasdaq composite index, which also closed at a record
high Monday, fell 10.32 to 1,401.72. It was weighed down by a drop
in several leading computer-related issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
